While identity is narrowed, federal power is deployed with new aggression against disfavored communities and regions. Operation Charlotte\'92s Web, launched by the Department of Homeland Security after local law enforcement refused to honor immigration detainers without warrants, brings Border Patrol and ICE into Charlotte and the Raleigh/Durham area in force. Over a weekend, agents in masks and unmarked cars arrest at least 81, and possibly over 130, people near churches, apartment complexes, and stores. Reports describe smashed car windows, a teenage grocery worker detained, and at least one U.S. citizen racially profiled and pulled from his vehicle. The operation is justified as a crackdown on \'93violent criminal illegal aliens,\'94 but court records from a similar Chicago sweep, Operation Midway Blitz, show that more than 97% of those detained there had no criminal convictions. The pattern is clear. Security forces are used to project federal power and create fear, not to surgically remove dangerous offenders.\
