The week also records a quieter but telling move by the State Department: an internal plan to suspend 38 universities, including Harvard and Yale, from the Diplomacy Lab research program because of their diversity, equity, and inclusion hiring practices. The memo proposes replacing them with institutions that adhere to \'93merit-based\'94 hiring as defined by the department. This is not a direct gag order. It uses federal partnership and funding as leverage to shape academic hiring norms and chill certain approaches to equity. Universities are put on notice that their internal policies can cost them access to federal programs if they do not align with the administration\'92s ideological preferences.\
